@lmannering please take a look at 7075b7ba5a999c9a74f11745a64afafa8569907c it demonstrates how to use OrderedDict with jsonpickle.  Let me know if you have any questions.  As others noted here, you have to construct OrderedDict using a list-of-tuples like the test case does otherwise the order is undefined (because it goes through a temporary python `{...}` dict that does not preserve order)..

We did have a bug when using `unpicklable=False` but that's now been fixed -- thanks for the heads-up!

That said, you probably don't want to use that flag ~ I'm guessing it was used while trying to debug this issue, perhaps?  In any case, it should be better behaved all-around.  The regular/default `unpicklable=True` code path was unaffected and was already working as intended.

